Note:
Runa Standard Library: AI Agent Registry Module

Provides comprehensive agent discovery, registration, and management capabilities for AI-to-AI communication.
Essential for multi-agent systems with robust agent discovery, service registration, and distributed coordination.

Advanced features include:
- Distributed registry coordination with consensus protocols
- Cryptographic identity verification and trust management
- Advanced load balancing with predictive scaling
- Real-time health monitoring and circuit breakers
- Performance optimization with intelligent caching
- Security with role-based access control and audit logging
- Fault tolerance with automatic failover and recovery
- Registry persistence with ACID compliance
- Advanced analytics and performance metrics
- Multi-region replication and disaster recovery
:End Note

Type AgentRegistry is Dictionary with:
    agents as Dictionary[String, AgentIdentity]
    capabilities_index as Dictionary[String, List[String]]
    health_status as Dictionary[String, Boolean]
    last_seen as Dictionary[String, Number]
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Dictionary[String, Any]]
    access_control as Dictionary[String, List[String]]
    load_balancing as Dictionary[String, Number]
    trust_scores as Dictionary[String, Number]
    performance_metrics as Dictionary[String, Dictionary[String, Number]]
    audit_log as List[Dictionary[String, Any]]
    distributed_state as Dictionary[String, Any]
    circuit_breakers as Dictionary[String, Dictionary[String, Any]]
    cache as Dictionary[String, Dictionary[String, Any]]
    security_policies as Dictionary[String, Dictionary[String, Any]]
    replication_state as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type RegistryEntry is Dictionary with:
    agent_id as String
    identity as AgentIdentity
    endpoint as String
    capabilities as List[String]
    health_status as Boolean
    last_heartbeat as Number
    load_factor as Number
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]
    trust_score as Number
    performance_metrics as Dictionary[String, Number]
    security_context as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type ServiceQuery is Dictionary with:
    required_capabilities as List[String]
    optional_capabilities as List[String]
    constraints as Dictionary[String, Any]
    load_preference as String
    timeout as Number
    max_results as Integer
    trust_threshold as Number
    performance_requirements as Dictionary[String, Number]
    security_requirements as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type RegistryFilter is Dictionary with:
    status_filter as String
    capability_filter as List[String]
    metadata_filter as Dictionary[String, Any]
    load_threshold as Number
    health_required as Boolean
    trust_threshold as Number
    performance_threshold as Dictionary[String, Number]

Type DistributedConsensus is Dictionary with:
    leader_id as String
    term as Number
    log as List[Dictionary[String, Any]]
    commit_index as Number
    last_applied as Number
    followers as Dictionary[String, Dictionary[String, Any]]
    election_timeout as Number
    heartbeat_interval as Number

Type CircuitBreaker is Dictionary with:
    failure_count as Number
    last_failure_time as Number
    state as String
    threshold as Number
    timeout as Number
    half_open_requests as Number
    success_threshold as Number

Type SecurityContext is Dictionary with:
    identity_verified as Boolean
    certificate_chain as List[String]
    permissions as List[String]
    audit_trail as List[Dictionary[String, Any]]
    encryption_keys as Dictionary[String, String]
    access_patterns as List[Dictionary[String, Any]]

